cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is primarily focused on language modeling, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new architecture for recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of pyramidal and grouped linear transformations in the PRU architecture may also be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) tasks.
